Package: MotionChart
Type: Package
Title: Flash-Free Animated Motion Charts via ECharts
Version: 0.9.0
Date: 2026-04-05
Author: John R. Wallace <soundbirds@comcast.net>
Maintainer: John R. Wallace <soundbirds@comcast.net>
Description: A flash-free replacement for googleVis::gvisMotionChart using
    echarts4r. Renders smooth, interactive animated bubble charts driven by a
    JavaScript requestAnimationFrame loop with client-side interpolation between
    real data time steps. Features include fading trail lines and ghost bubbles,
    interactive play/pause/scrub controls, hover and click entity highlighting,
    legend-based group filtering, live label size adjustment, and a pinned
    tooltip. All animation logic runs in the browser; data remains local.
    Calls originate from R and output is an htmlwidget suitable for use in
    RStudio, Shiny, R Markdown, and Quarto.
License: MIT
URL: https://github.com/John-R-Wallace-NOAA/GoogleVis_Type_Motion_Chart_No_Flash
BugReports: https://github.com/John-R-Wallace-NOAA/GoogleVis_Type_Motion_Chart_No_Flash/issues
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    echarts4r (>= 0.4.0),
    dplyr,
    htmlwidgets,
    jsonlite,
    htmltools
Suggests:
    gapminder,
    stringr,
    remotes
